title: Mystery at Geneva: An Improbable Tale of Singular Happenings
creator: Dame Rose Macaulay
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Mystery at Geneva: An Improbable Tale of Singular Happenings, by Dame Rose Macaulay. Read by Cathy Barratt. Henry Beechtree, a newspaper correspondent for the British Bolshevist, is covering the latest otherwise sleepy session of the League of Nations in Geneva, when the newly elected President – a member of the Norwegian delegation – disappears mysteriously, adding some badly needed ‘spice’ to Henry's assignment. (Introduction by Cathy Barratt) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (113MB)
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; adventure; fiction; mystery
